== Buried Individual ==

<div class="thumb tright">
 <div style="margin: 0px; padding: 2px; border: 1px solid #a2a9b1; text-align: center; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%; text-align:center; font-size:80%">
'''Isonokami Clan Genealogy'''
{{familytree/start|style="text-align:left; font-size:100%"}}
{{familytree|border=0|||||||01| 01={{ill|Isonokami Maro|ja|石上麻呂}}<br/>(Senior Second Rank, Minister of the Left, 640–717)}}
{{familytree|border=0|||||||!|}}
{{familytree|border=0|||||||01| 01={{ill|Isonokami Otomaro|ja|石上乙麻呂}}<br/>(Junior Third Rank, Middle Councillor, ?–750)}}
{{familytree|border=0|||||||!|}}
{{familytree|border=0|||||||01| 01={{ill|Isonokami no Yakatsugu|ja|石上宅嗣}}<br/>(Senior Third Rank, Councillor, 729–781)}}
{{familytree/end}}
</div></div>

The buried individual is unidentified but believed to be a high-ranking aristocrat of the Isonokami clan. Proposed identities include:

* '''Isonokami no Yakatsugu''' (d. 781): This theory has been suggested since the publication of the excavation report, considering the individual's high rank during the Nara period.
* '''Isonokami Maro''' (d. 717): This recent theory compares the tomb's scale to that of the {{ill|Kojitada no Yasumaro Cremation Tomb|ja|小治田安萬侶の墓}} (Nara City). The tomb's size, robust tamped-earth construction, and associated artifacts suggest it predates Empress Genmei's 721 decree for simpler burials{{Sfn|Hino Hiroshi|2021}}.

